On the Noether Dualization Method. 

Note the Maxwell term remain unafected under dualization and this
could be not considered ().
This seems to be a characteristic of gauge invariant terms in the
initial action.
Notice further that
in the particular limit , the action  is, in certain
sense,
a parent action for this duality, this is a frecuent
behavior of this dualization method.
To prove this, we
only must note that the last iterated lagrangian () is
precisely the so-called parent action . In other words, we
must show that by varying this with respect, first to  and
second to , the actions () and () are recovered.

Varying  with respect to , by construction (In
fact, this constitutes the final step of the Gauging Noether
