The study of the three remaining poles brings about an interesting result: the residues found for the poles coming from the massless factor of  are simply the residues found for the massless theory up to  a minus sign. This suggest that maybe the total propagator can be rearranged so as to be expressed as the difference between the
propagators of the massive and the non-massive theories. Indeed, we have:
A_A_A_A__1-A_A__2
